## Task 2 Basic Packet Capture

- Specify Interface: -i INTERFACE (e.g., -i eth0, -i any).
- Save Packets: -w FILE saves to .pcap.
- Read Packets: -r FILE reads from saved capture.
- Limit Count: -c COUNT captures a fixed number.
- Disable Resolution: -n disables DNS lookups, -nn disables DNS + port resolution.
- Verbose Output: -v, -vv, -vvv increase detail.
Examples
- tcpdump -i eth0 -c 50 -v → capture 50 packets on eth0, verbose.
- tcpdump -i wlo1 -w data.pcap → capture on WiFi, save to file.
- tcpdump -i any -nn → capture all interfaces, no resolution.

