## Task 3 Filtering Expressions

- Filters allow focusing on relevant traffic.
By Host:
- tcpdump host example.com -w http.pcap → capture traffic with example.com.
- src host / dst host limit to source/destination.
By Port:
- tcpdump port 53 → capture DNS traffic.
- src port / dst port limit to source/destination port.
By Protocol:
- tcpdump icmp → capture ICMP packets (ping, traceroute).
- Other options: ip, ip6, tcp, udp.
- Logical Operators:
- and, or, not combine conditions.
Example: tcpdump host 1.1.1.1 and tcp.
- Offline Analysis:
- tcpdump -r traffic.pcap src host 192.168.124.1 -n | wc → count packets from source IP.

---

## Task 4 Advanced Filtering

- Advanced filters allow precise selection.
- Length Filters:
- greater LENGTH → packets ≥ length.
- less LENGTH → packets ≤ length.
Binary Operations:
- & (AND), | (OR), ! (NOT).
- Header Bytes:
- Syntax: proto[expr:size].
Example: ether[0] & 1 != 0 → multicast packets.
Example: ip[0] & 0xf != 5 → IP packets with options.
- TCP Flags Filtering:
- tcp[tcpflags] == tcp-syn → only SYN.
- tcp[tcpflags] & tcp-syn != 0 → packets with SYN set.
- tcp[tcpflags] & (tcp-syn|tcp-ack) != 0 → SYN or ACK set.

