## Tools Used

- Tcpdump with options (-i, -w, -r, -c, -n, -v, -q, -e, -A, -xx, -X).
- Libpcap library.
- Wireshark/Tshark for complementary analysis.

## Findings

- Tcpdump provides lightweight, fast packet capture.
- Filters (host, port, protocol, flags) allow precise targeting.
- Display options adapt output to analysis needs.
- Offline analysis with .pcap files enhances flexibility.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Always specify interface to avoid missing traffic.
- Save captures for later analysis.
- Use filters to reduce noise.
- Disable resolution (-nn) for performance.
- Apply verbose output when deeper inspection is needed.
- Use ASCII/hex display depending on traffic type.

